PART: Budget Tracker
NAME: Budget Tracker
STATUS: draft

DATA: Budget Categories
MARKER: budget_categories
INTENT: holds all budget categories and their balances
TAGS: #list
---
The app holds a list of budget categories. Each category has a name, a current balance, and a monthly limit.

STRUCTURE: Dashboard Screen
MARKER: dashboard_screen
INTENT: the main screen showing budget categories and totals
---
The screen has a header with the app name, a section for each budget category with its name, balance, and limit, and a summary at the bottom with total income and expenses.

WHEN: Add Category
MARKER: add_category
INTENT: user adds a new budget category
TAGS: #form, #list, #user
---
When the user taps the "Add Category" button, a form appears. The user fills in the category name and limit. The new category appears in the list with a zero balance.

ASSERT: Category Limits
MARKER: category_limits
INTENT: validation for category limits
TAGS: #user
---
A category limit cannot be negative. A user can only edit their own category limits.

SURFACE: Category Card
MARKER: category_card
INTENT: labels and styles for category cards
TAGS: #card
---
The category card displays the category name, current balance, and limit. The balance is shown in green if positive, red if negative, and gray if zero. The limit is shown as a line with a percentage filled.